Mark Heywood, editor of Maverick Citizen, spoke with eNCA's Faith Mangope. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG – The head of the Ministerial Advisory Committee on Vaccines, Professor Barry Schoub, says they may consider suspending use of the AstraZeneca vaccine. That's after a Wits University study found that the vaccine appears to be less effective against the Covid-19 variant first discovered in South Africa. WATCH: Mkhize and health experts give vaccine update This comes as the country prepares to roll out this vaccine. Schoub says they need to look at a combination of vaccines that may give a good response against the variant.